Reasoning: The paper deals with the task of detecting foiled image captions, which requires a fine-grained understanding of images to detect linguistically valid perturbations in captions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also proposes models based on explicit object information, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves measuring the upper-bound performance of the models using gold standard annotations, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
